DescDetail: <<
 In addition to common and advanced GUI facilities such as
 frames, scrolling windows, toolbars, tree controls, icons,
 device contexts, printing, splitter windows and so on, there are
 wrappers for common file operations, and facilities for writing
 TCP/IP applications, thread handling, and more. Where certain
 features are not available on a platform, such as MDI and tree
 controls on Unix, they are emulated.
<<
DescPort: <<
Doesn't build with clang, so force llvm-g++, at least for now.

Uses some items that have been removed from Lion's Cocoa, so we need the
10.6 SDK:
	
http://old.nabble.com/-MacPorts---30272%3A-wxWidgets-failes-on-10.7
-td32107053.html#a32107053

Because the QuickTime library is i386 only, forcibly rip out any attempts
to link to it on x86_64.
<<
